2.2 Information Extraction Metadata extraction can be viewed as an application of information extraction, in which given a sequence of instances, we identify a subsequence that represents information in which we are interested.
[16] also conducted automatic metadata extraction from research papers using rules on formatting information.
They reported high extraction accuracy from research papers in terms of precision and recall.
Liddy et al.
managed to extract titles from research papers and make use of the extracted titles in metadata search of papers [8].
However, it also has disadvantages.
